The paper proposes a solution to the credit assignment problem in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in the field of neural networks and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the ventral visual pathway, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves deep neural networks with feedforward, lateral, and feedback connections, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of a supervised learning algorithm, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of biologically-plausible Hebbian and anti-Hebbian plasticity, which is a topic in the field of systems and control (cs.SY).
